      "category": "grammar",
      "errorExample": "I student.",
      "correctForm": "I am a student.",
      "explanation": "In English, you must use the verb 'be' (am/is/are) and an article 'a' before the noun.",
      "tip": "한국어에서는 '나 학생이야'라고 be동사 없이 말하지만, 영어는 꼭 am/is/are가 필요해요!"
    },
    {
      "id": "pack-000001:korean-error-002",
      "category": "pronunciation",
      "errorExample": "My name is 'Toom'",
      "correctForm": "My name is 'Tom' /tɑːm/",
      "explanation": "The 'o' in 'Tom' is a short vowel, not a long 'oo' sound.",
      "tip": "'Tom'은 '톰'이지 '툼'이 아니에요. 입을 크게 벌리고 짧게 발음하세요."
    },
    {
      "id": "pack-000001:korean-error-003",
      "category": "usage",
      "errorExample": "Hello. I am Tom. Hello again.",
      "correctForm": "Hello. I am Tom. Nice to meet you.",
      "explanation": "When introducing yourself, don't repeat 'Hello'. Use 'Nice to meet you' instead.",
      "tip": "자기소개할 때 'Hello'를 반복하지 말고 'Nice to meet you'로 마무리하세요."
